<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="305" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,414,981]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,414,441]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species appears to be distributed throughout the northern GOM in offshore waters ranging from approximately 100 to over 
<quantity box="[468,556,451,477]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
in depth (C. Jones, unpublished data). The two sightings reported from the Flower Garden Banks (
<bibRefCitation author="Childs, J. N." box="[409,547,487,513]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref16400" refString="Childs, J. N. (1997) Range extension of Mobula tarapacana into the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Gulf of Mexico Science, 15 (1), 39 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / goms. 1501.05" type="journal article" year="1997">Childs 1997</bibRefCitation>
, see below) both occurred during the month of August and both were associated with annual water temperature maxima and coral spawning events. This may mean that while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walbaum" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[1215,1388,523,549]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Manta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="birostris">
<emphasis box="[1215,1388,523,549]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Manta birostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bancroft" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[151,364,559,585]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Mobula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypostoma">
<emphasis box="[151,364,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Mobula hypostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are year round residents at the West Flower Garden Banks (see distributional remarks for those species above), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[322,540,595,621]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Myliobatidae" genus="Mobula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tarapacana">
<emphasis box="[322,540,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Mobula tarapacana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could utilize the area only for feeding during annual coral spawning events (
<bibRefCitation author="Childs, J. N." pageId="24" pageNumber="305" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref16400" refString="Childs, J. N. (1997) Range extension of Mobula tarapacana into the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Gulf of Mexico Science, 15 (1), 39 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / goms. 1501.05" type="journal article" year="1997">Childs 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,414,981]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,666,693]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
The first record of this species in the northern GOM is a report by 
<bibRefCitation author="Childs, J. N." box="[1224,1379,667,693]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref16400" refString="Childs, J. N. (1997) Range extension of Mobula tarapacana into the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Gulf of Mexico Science, 15 (1), 39 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / goms. 1501.05" type="journal article" year="1997">Childs (1997)</bibRefCitation>
concerning a single individual captured on video during a monthly observation dive on the West Flower Garden Bank in August of 1993. In the same publication 
<bibRefCitation author="Childs, J. N." box="[602,756,739,765]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref16400" refString="Childs, J. N. (1997) Range extension of Mobula tarapacana into the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Gulf of Mexico Science, 15 (1), 39 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / goms. 1501.05" type="journal article" year="1997">Childs (1997)</bibRefCitation>
documents a second sighting, also from West Flower Garden Bank, from August of 1995.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="305" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,414,981]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,811,837]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Remarks.</emphasis>
Since it was first reported from the northern GOM (
<bibRefCitation author="Childs, J. N." box="[926,1068,811,837]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref16400" refString="Childs, J. N. (1997) Range extension of Mobula tarapacana into the northwestern Gulf of Mexico. Gulf of Mexico Science, 15 (1), 39 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.18785 / goms. 1501.05" type="journal article" year="1997">Childs 1997</bibRefCitation>
) this species has been observed several times, predominantly in West 
<collectingRegion box="[567,648,847,873]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Florida</collectingRegion>
Shelf waters during aerial surveys conducted by the NMFS SEFSC (C. Jones, unpublished data) from 
<date box="[497,649,883,909]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305" value="1996" valueMax="1998">1996 to 1998</date>
. This species is encountered as bycatch in the pelagic longline fishery in the northern GOM (
<figureCitation box="[403,515,918,945]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1958,1983]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,1002,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[174,1412,1002,1933]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 15. Mobula tarapacana captured by pelagic longline in the northern Gulf of Mexico. Photograph courtesy of NMFS SEFSC." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909143/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Figure 15</figureCitation>
, C. Jones unpublished data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,414,981]" box="[199,578,954,981]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,954,981]" pageId="24" pageNumber="305">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Vulnerable
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
